      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLATTERED (4) has a strong record this track and trip with five wins and four placings from 13 starts. Recorded a 3.5 lengths win (19.98) in a Grade 4/5 last time at this track. Looks well placed and should feature. LORD PANAMA (1) looks close to another win after finishing third from Box 7 last time (20.00) at this track. Has a strong record out of this box with three wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Overdue and is among the main hopes. CAMBRIDGE KING (7) boasts a consistent overall record including 11 wins from 43 starts, the latest hitting the minor money when third (21.04) over 365m at Nowra. Form at this distance is sound. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. LOW BEAM (2) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
